cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of Random Linear Network Coding (RLNC) in wired erasure networks with finite buffers. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of the performance of RLNC, which is a coding technique used in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper models the performance of the network using Markov chains, which is a technique used in systems and control. 
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper is concerned with analyzing the performance of RLNC in finite buffer networks. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the performance of RLNC in networks, which can be considered as a form of distributed computing.
